@startuml

title User Inventory Add to Cart Sequence Diagram

actor User

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "CartController" as CC
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of User
It is assumed the User is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note


== Open Borrow Modal ==

User -> FE: Click "Pedir Prestado" on selected item
activate User
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate CC
activate ORM
activate DB

FE -> FE: Load selected item data into borrow modal
note right of FE
Populate modal with:
- equipment_id
- item name
- image
- available stock
- default quantity = 1
end note

alt Item has available stock
    FE --> User: Display borrow modal
else Item unavailable
    FE --> User: Borrow button remains disabled
end


== Validate Quantity ==

User -> FE: Enter requested quantity

alt Quantity is empty
    FE --> User: Display "Debes pedir al menos 1 unidad."
else Quantity is not numeric
    FE --> User: Display "Debes ingresar un número válido."
else Quantity is less than 1
    FE --> User: Display "Debes pedir al menos 1 unidad."
else Quantity exceeds available stock
    FE --> User: Display "No puedes pedir más de {stock} unidades disponibles."
else Quantity valid
    FE --> User: Keep quantity field valid
end


== Add Item to Cart ==

User -> FE: Click "Añadir al Carrito"
FE -> Apache: POST /cart/add

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP add-to-cart request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> User: Display "Add to cart route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> CC: Pass authenticated and authorized add-to-cart request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden / 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> User: Display validation or authorization error
end

CC -> ORM: Load equipment by submitted equipment_id
ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM equipment WHERE id = ? LIMIT 1

alt Equipment found
    DB --> ORM: Equipment record
    ORM --> CC: Equipment retrieved
else Equipment not found
    DB --> ORM: Empty result set
    ORM --> CC: Equipment not found
    CC --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> User: Display selected equipment not found error
end

CC -> CC: Validate requested quantity against available stock

alt Requested quantity valid
    CC -> CC: Add or update equipment entry in session cart
    CC --> FE: Redirect back with cart success message
    FE --> User: Show cart success confirmation "Item añadido al carrito"
else Requested quantity invalid
    CC --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity / Redirect back with validation error
    FE --> User: Display quantity validation error
end

@enduml